FROM (VALUES
  ('sandbag-bear-hug-squat-strength', 'Bear-hug loading forces the athlete to create whole-body tension while squatting through a usable range without relying on a rigid bar path.', 'Belongs in Capacity because the exercise uses progressive loaded work to build strength, force production, tissue tolerance, and structural reserve.', 'Capacity phase after Output/power work and before late conditioning; use after athletes are warm enough to load safely.', 'The main mistake is turning the card into a race, finisher, or sloppy high-rep circuit. Keep load, reps, and rest aligned with strength, not exhaustion.', 'Scale first by load and range, then by tempo, leverage, distance, or support. Progress only when first and last reps look the same.'),
